    • Method Detail

      • generateArtificialSolution

        protected List<Matching> generateArtificialSolution()
        Generates an artificial solution. Columns in the artificial solution are of high cost such that they never end up in the final solution if a feasible solution exists, since any feasible solution is assumed to be cheaper than the artificial solution. The artificial solution is used to guarantee that the master problem has a feasible solution.
        Specified by:
        generateArtificialSolution in class AbstractBranchAndPrice<TSP,Matching,PricingProblemByColor>
        Returns:
        artificial solution
